Note:
Runa Standard Library: GZIP Compression Module

Provides production-ready gzip compression and decompression functionality compatible with
RFC 1952 (GZIP file format) and RFC 1951 (DEFLATE compressed data format). Supports both
data compression and file operations with comprehensive error handling and performance optimization.

Features:
- Industry-standard GZIP compression with RFC 1952 compliance
- DEFLATE algorithm implementation following RFC 1951 specification
- Stream-based compression for large files and real-time processing
- Memory-efficient buffered operations for handling large datasets
- Comprehensive error handling with detailed diagnostics
- Progress tracking for long-running compression operations
- Thread-safe operations for concurrent compression tasks
- Integration with Runa's advanced type system for type safety
- Performance optimization with adaptive compression strategies
- CRC32 checksum verification for data integrity validation
- Compatible with standard gzip tools and libraries
- Support for multiple compression levels (1-9)
- Optional compression of file metadata (timestamps, original filename)

Technical specifications:
- Compression levels: 1 (fast) to 9 (best compression), default 6
- Window size: 32KB (fixed for GZIP compatibility)
- Memory usage: Configurable based on compression level and buffer size
- Thread safety: All operations are thread-safe and reentrant
- Error recovery: Robust error handling with recovery suggestions
- CRC32: IEEE 802.3 polynomial for integrity verification
:End Note

Note: Core GZIP Types and Configuration
Type called "GZIPConfig":
    compression_level as Integer defaults to 6
    enable_crc_check as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_progress_tracking as Boolean defaults to false
    buffer_size as Integer defaults to 65536
    enable_parallel_compression as Boolean defaults to false
    thread_count as Integer defaults to 1
    preserve_filename as Boolean defaults to false
    preserve_timestamp as Boolean defaults to false
    original_filename as Optional[String] defaults to None
    compression_strategy as String defaults to "default"
    window_bits as Integer defaults to 15
    memory_level as Integer defaults to 8
    enable_stream_mode as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type GZIPCompressResult is:
    | GZIPCompressSuccess with compressed_data as List[Integer] and original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and compression_ratio as Float and crc32 as String and header_info as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | GZIPCompressError with error_message as String and error_code as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type GZIPDecompressResult is:
    | GZIPDecompressSuccess with decompressed_data as String and original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and crc32_valid as Boolean and header_info as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | GZIPDecompressError with error_message as String and error_code as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type GZIPFileResult is:
    | GZIPFileSuccess with file_path as String and operation as String and bytes_processed as Integer and processing_time as Float and compression_ratio as Float
    | GZIPFileError with error_message as String and error_code as String and file_path as String and suggestions as List[String]

Type called "GZIPStreamContext":
    config as GZIPConfig
    stream_state as Dictionary[String, Any]
    bytes_processed as Integer
    total_input_size as Integer
    total_output_size as Integer
    crc32_checksum as String
    deflate_state as Dictionary[String, Any]
    is_finished as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "GZIPHeader":
    magic_number as List[Integer]
    compression_method as Integer
    flags as Integer
    timestamp as Integer
    extra_flags as Integer
    operating_system as Integer
    original_filename as Optional[String]
    comment as Optional[String]
    crc16 as Optional[Integer]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DeflateConfig":
    compression_level as Integer defaults to 6
    window_bits as Integer defaults to 15
    memory_level as Integer defaults to 8
    strategy as String defaults to "default"
    buffer_size as Integer defaults to 32768
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Core GZIP Compression Functions
Process called "gzip_compress" that takes data as String and config as Optional[GZIPConfig] returns GZIPCompressResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_gzip_config
    
    Try:
        If length of data is equal to 0:
            Return GZIPCompressError with:
                error_message as "Cannot compress empty data"
                error_code as "GZIP_EMPTY_INPUT"
                suggestions as list containing "Provide non-empty input data"
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as 0
        
        Let validation_result be validate_gzip_config with config as final_config
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return GZIPCompressError with:
                error_message as "Invalid GZIP configuration: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "GZIP_INVALID_CONFIG"
                suggestions as validation_result.suggestions
                context as dictionary containing "config" as final_config
        
        Let input_bytes be convert_string_to_bytes with data as data
        Let original_size be length of input_bytes
        
        Let gzip_header be create_gzip_header with config as final_config and original_size as original_size
        Let deflate_config be create_deflate_config_from_gzip_config with config as final_config
        
        Let deflate_result be deflate_compress with data as input_bytes and config as deflate_config
        If deflate_result is None:
            Return GZIPCompressError with:
                error_message as "DEFLATE compression failed"
                error_code as "GZIP_DEFLATE_FAILED"
                suggestions as list containing "Check input data validity", "Try different compression level", "Verify available memory"
                context as dictionary containing "original_size" as original_size
        
        Let crc32_checksum be calculate_crc32 with data as input_bytes
        Let gzip_trailer be create_gzip_trailer with crc32 as crc32_checksum and original_size as original_size
        
        Let compressed_data be concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing gzip_header, deflate_result, gzip_trailer
        Let compressed_size be length of compressed_data
        Let compression_ratio be calculate_compression_ratio with original_size as original_size and compressed_size as compressed_size
        
        Let header_info be extract_header_info_from_gzip_header with header as gzip_header
        
        Return GZIPCompressSuccess with:
            compressed_data as compressed_data
            original_size as original_size
            compressed_size as compressed_size
            compression_ratio as compression_ratio
            crc32 as crc32_checksum
            header_info as header_info
    
    Catch error:
        Return GZIPCompressError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected GZIP compression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "GZIP_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify input data encoding", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "gzip_decompress" that takes compressed_data as List[Integer] and config as Optional[GZIPConfig] returns GZIPDecompressResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_gzip_config
    
    Try:
        If length of compressed_data is equal to 0:
            Return GZIPDecompressError with:
                error_message as "Cannot decompress empty data"
                error_code as "GZIP_EMPTY_COMPRESSED_DATA"
                suggestions as list containing "Provide valid compressed data"
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as 0
        
        Let validation_result be validate_gzip_data with data as compressed_data
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return GZIPDecompressError with:
                error_message as "Invalid GZIP data format: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "GZIP_INVALID_DATA"
                suggestions as validation_result.suggestions
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as length of compressed_data
        
        Let gzip_parts be parse_gzip_data with data as compressed_data
        If gzip_parts is None:
            Return GZIPDecompressError with:
                error_message as "Failed to parse GZIP data structure"
                error_code as "GZIP_PARSE_FAILED"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify data is valid GZIP format", "Check for data corruption"
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as length of compressed_data
        
        Let header_info be extract_header_info_from_gzip_header with header as gzip_parts.header
        Let deflate_config be create_deflate_config_from_gzip_config with config as final_config
        
        Let deflate_result be deflate_decompress with data as gzip_parts.compressed_data and config as deflate_config
        If deflate_result is None:
            Return GZIPDecompressError with:
                error_message as "DEFLATE decompression failed"
                error_code as "GZIP_DEFLATE_DECOMPRESS_FAILED"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify compressed data integrity", "Check data is valid DEFLATE format"
                context as dictionary containing "compressed_size" as length of gzip_parts.compressed_data
        
        Let decompressed_data be convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as deflate_result
        Let original_size be length of deflate_result
        
        Let crc32_valid be true
        If final_config.enable_crc_check:
            Let calculated_crc32 be calculate_crc32 with data as deflate_result
            Let expected_crc32 be extract_crc32_from_trailer with trailer as gzip_parts.trailer
            Set crc32_valid to calculated_crc32 is equal to expected_crc32
        
        Let expected_size be extract_original_size_from_trailer with trailer as gzip_parts.trailer
        If expected_size is not equal to original_size:
            Return GZIPDecompressError with:
                error_message as "Size mismatch: expected " plus expected_size plus ", got " plus original_size
                error_code as "GZIP_SIZE_MISMATCH"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify data integrity", "Check for truncated file"
                context as dictionary containing "expected_size" as expected_size, "actual_size" as original_size
        
        Return GZIPDecompressSuccess with:
            decompressed_data as decompressed_data
            original_size as original_size
            compressed_size as length of compressed_data
            crc32_valid as crc32_valid
            header_info as header_info
    
    Catch error:
        Return GZIPDecompressError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected GZIP decompression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "GZIP_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify compressed data format", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "gzip_compress_file" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and config as Optional[GZIPConfig] returns GZIPFileResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_gzip_config
    
    Try:
        Let file_exists be check_file_exists with path as input_path
        If not file_exists:
            Return GZIPFileError with:
                error_message as "Input file does not exist: " plus input_path
                error_code as "GZIP_FILE_NOT_FOUND"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let file_size be get_file_size with path as input_path
        If file_size is equal to 0:
            Return GZIPFileError with:
                error_message as "Cannot compress empty file: " plus input_path
                error_code as "GZIP_EMPTY_FILE"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Provide non-empty input file"
        
        Let output_dir be get_directory_from_path with path as output_path
        Let dir_exists be ensure_directory_exists with path as output_dir
        If not dir_exists:
            Return GZIPFileError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create output directory: " plus output_dir
                error_code as "GZIP_OUTPUT_DIR_ERROR"
                file_path as output_path
                suggestions as list containing "Check directory permissions", "Verify path is valid"
        
        If final_config.preserve_filename and final_config.original_filename is None:
            Let filename be get_filename_from_path with path as input_path
            Set final_config.original_filename to filename
        
        Let compression_result be compress_file_with_gzip with:
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            config as final_config
        
        Match compression_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return GZIPFileSuccess with:
                    file_path as output_path
                    operation as "compress"
                    bytes_processed as compression_result.bytes_processed
                    processing_time as processing_time
                    compression_ratio as compression_result.compression_ratio
            
            When "error":
                Return GZIPFileError with:
                    error_message as compression_result.error_message
                    error_code as compression_result.error_code
                    file_path as input_path
                    suggestions as compression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return GZIPFileError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected file compression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "GZIP_FILE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            file_path as input_path
            suggestions as list containing "Check file permissions", "Verify disk space", "Report this as a bug"

Process called "gzip_decompress_file" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and config as Optional[GZIPConfig] returns GZIPFileResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_gzip_config
    
    Try:
        Let file_exists be check_file_exists with path as input_path
        If not file_exists:
            Return GZIPFileError with:
                error_message as "Input file does not exist: " plus input_path
                error_code as "GZIP_FILE_NOT_FOUND"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let is_gzip_file be validate_gzip_file_format with path as input_path
        If not is_gzip_file:
            Return GZIPFileError with:
                error_message as "File is not a valid GZIP compressed file: " plus input_path
                error_code as "GZIP_INVALID_FILE_FORMAT"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file is GZIP compressed", "Check file extension is .gz"
        
        Let output_dir be get_directory_from_path with path as output_path
        Let dir_exists be ensure_directory_exists with path as output_dir
        If not dir_exists:
            Return GZIPFileError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create output directory: " plus output_dir
                error_code as "GZIP_OUTPUT_DIR_ERROR"
                file_path as output_path
                suggestions as list containing "Check directory permissions", "Verify path is valid"
        
        Let decompression_result be decompress_file_with_gzip with:
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            config as final_config
        
        Match decompression_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return GZIPFileSuccess with:
                    file_path as output_path
                    operation as "decompress"
                    bytes_processed as decompression_result.bytes_processed
                    processing_time as processing_time
                    compression_ratio as decompression_result.compression_ratio
            
            When "error":
                Return GZIPFileError with:
                    error_message as decompression_result.error_message
                    error_code as decompression_result.error_code
                    file_path as input_path
                    suggestions as decompression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return GZIPFileError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected file decompression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "GZIP_FILE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            file_path as input_path
            suggestions as list containing "Check file permissions", "Verify disk space", "Report this as a bug"
:End Note

Note: Stream-based GZIP Operations
Process called "gzip_create_compression_stream" that takes config as Optional[GZIPConfig] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_gzip_config
    
    Let stream_context be GZIPStreamContext with:
        config as final_config
        stream_state as dictionary containing "initialized" as false, "mode" as "compress", "header_written" as false
        bytes_processed as 0
        total_input_size as 0
        total_output_size as 0
        crc32_checksum as ""
        deflate_state as dictionary containing
        is_finished as false
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_time" as get_current_time
    
    Let initialization_result be initialize_gzip_compression_stream with context as stream_context
    If not initialization_result.success:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as initialization_result.error_message
            "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_INIT_FAILED"
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as true
        "stream_context" as stream_context
        "stream_id" as generate_gzip_stream_id

Process called "gzip_compress_stream_data" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] and data as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context["is_finished"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot add data to finished compression stream"
                "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_FINISHED"
        
        Let input_bytes be convert_string_to_bytes with data as data
        Let input_size be length of input_bytes
        Let output_data be list containing
        
        If not stream_context["stream_state"]["header_written"]:
            Let gzip_header be create_gzip_header with config as stream_context["config"] and original_size as -1
            Set output_data to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing output_data, gzip_header
            Set stream_context["stream_state"]["header_written"] to true
        
        Let deflate_result be deflate_compress_chunk with:
            deflate_state as stream_context["deflate_state"]
            input_data as input_bytes
        
        If deflate_result.success:
            Set output_data to concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing output_data, deflate_result.output_data
            Set stream_context["bytes_processed"] to stream_context["bytes_processed"] plus input_size
            Set stream_context["total_input_size"] to stream_context["total_input_size"] plus input_size
            Set stream_context["total_output_size"] to stream_context["total_output_size"] plus length of output_data
            
            Let current_crc32 be calculate_crc32_incremental with:
                previous_crc32 as stream_context["crc32_checksum"]
                data as input_bytes
            Set stream_context["crc32_checksum"] to current_crc32
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "compressed_data" as output_data
                "bytes_processed" as input_size
                "total_compressed_size" as stream_context["total_output_size"]
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as deflate_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_COMPRESS_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream compression error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_INTERNAL_ERROR"

Process called "gzip_finish_compression_stream" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context["is_finished"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Compression stream already finished"
                "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_ALREADY_FINISHED"
        
        Let finalization_result be finalize_deflate_compression with deflate_state as stream_context["deflate_state"]
        
        If finalization_result.success:
            Let gzip_trailer be create_gzip_trailer with:
                crc32 as stream_context["crc32_checksum"]
                original_size as stream_context["total_input_size"]
            
            Let final_data be concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing finalization_result.final_data, gzip_trailer
            
            Set stream_context["is_finished"] to true
            Set stream_context["total_output_size"] to stream_context["total_output_size"] plus length of final_data
            
            Let compression_ratio be calculate_compression_ratio with:
                original_size as stream_context["total_input_size"]
                compressed_size as stream_context["total_output_size"]
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "final_compressed_data" as final_data
                "total_input_size" as stream_context["total_input_size"]
                "total_output_size" as stream_context["total_output_size"]
                "compression_ratio" as compression_ratio
                "crc32" as stream_context["crc32_checksum"]
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as finalization_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_FINALIZE_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream finalization error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_FINALIZE_INTERNAL_ERROR"

Process called "gzip_create_decompression_stream" that takes config as Optional[GZIPConfig] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_gzip_config
    
    Let stream_context be GZIPStreamContext with:
        config as final_config
        stream_state as dictionary containing "initialized" as false, "mode" as "decompress", "header_parsed" as false
        bytes_processed as 0
        total_input_size as 0
        total_output_size as 0
        crc32_checksum as ""
        deflate_state as dictionary containing
        is_finished as false
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_time" as get_current_time
    
    Let initialization_result be initialize_gzip_decompression_stream with context as stream_context
    If not initialization_result.success:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as initialization_result.error_message
            "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_INIT_FAILED"
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as true
        "stream_context" as stream_context
        "stream_id" as generate_gzip_stream_id

Process called "gzip_decompress_stream_data" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] and compressed_data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context["is_finished"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot add data to finished decompression stream"
                "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_FINISHED"
        
        Let input_size be length of compressed_data
        Let remaining_data be compressed_data
        Let output_data be ""
        
        If not stream_context["stream_state"]["header_parsed"]:
            Let header_parse_result be parse_gzip_header_from_stream with data as remaining_data
            If header_parse_result.success:
                Set stream_context["stream_state"]["header_parsed"] to true
                Set stream_context["stream_state"]["header_info"] to header_parse_result.header_info
                Set remaining_data to header_parse_result.remaining_data
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "error_message" as "Failed to parse GZIP header"
                    "error_code" as "GZIP_HEADER_PARSE_ERROR"
        
        If length of remaining_data is greater than 0:
            Let deflate_result be deflate_decompress_chunk with:
                deflate_state as stream_context["deflate_state"]
                compressed_data as remaining_data
            
            If deflate_result.success:
                Set output_data to convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as deflate_result.output_data
                Set stream_context["bytes_processed"] to stream_context["bytes_processed"] plus input_size
                Set stream_context["total_input_size"] to stream_context["total_input_size"] plus input_size
                Set stream_context["total_output_size"] to stream_context["total_output_size"] plus length of deflate_result.output_data
                
                Let current_crc32 be calculate_crc32_incremental with:
                    previous_crc32 as stream_context["crc32_checksum"]
                    data as deflate_result.output_data
                Set stream_context["crc32_checksum"] to current_crc32
                
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as true
                    "decompressed_data" as output_data
                    "bytes_processed" as input_size
                    "total_decompressed_size" as stream_context["total_output_size"]
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "error_message" as deflate_result.error_message
                    "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_DECOMPRESS_ERROR"
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "decompressed_data" as output_data
            "bytes_processed" as input_size
            "total_decompressed_size" as stream_context["total_output_size"]
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream decompression error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "GZIP_STREAM_INTERNAL_ERROR"
:End Note

Note: DEFLATE Algorithm Implementation
Process called "deflate_compress" that takes data as List[Integer] and config as DeflateConfig returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        Let deflate_context be initialize_deflate_compression with config as config
        
        Let lz77_result be lz77_compress with data as data and window_size as 32768
        If lz77_result is None:
            Return None
        
        Let huffman_result be huffman_encode with data as lz77_result and compression_level as config.compression_level
        If huffman_result is None:
            Return None
        
        Let final_result be finalize_deflate_block with data as huffman_result
        Return final_result
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "deflate_decompress" that takes data as List[Integer] and config as DeflateConfig returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        Let deflate_context be initialize_deflate_decompression with config as config
        
        Let huffman_result be huffman_decode with data as data
        If huffman_result is None:
            Return None
        
        Let lz77_result be lz77_decompress with data as huffman_result and window_size as 32768
        If lz77_result is None:
            Return None
        
        Return lz77_result
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "lz77_compress" that takes data as List[Integer] and window_size as Integer returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Note: LZ77 sliding window compression algorithm implementation
    Let compressed be list containing
    Let window_start be 0
    Let current_position be 0
    
    While current_position is less than length of data:
        Let best_match be find_longest_match with:
            data as data
            current_position as current_position
            window_start as window_start
            window_size as window_size
        
        If best_match.length is greater than 3:
            Let distance_length_pair be create_distance_length_pair with:
                distance as best_match.distance
                length as best_match.length
            Add distance_length_pair to compressed
            Set current_position to current_position plus best_match.length
        Otherwise:
            Let literal_byte be data[current_position]
            Add literal_byte to compressed
            Set current_position to current_position plus 1
        
        If current_position minus window_start is greater than window_size:
            Set window_start to current_position minus window_size
    
    Return compressed

Process called "lz77_decompress" that takes data as List[Integer] and window_size as Integer returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Note: LZ77 sliding window decompression algorithm implementation
    Let decompressed be list containing
    Let position be 0
    
    While position is less than length of data:
        Let element be data[position]
        
        If is_distance_length_pair with element as element:
            Let pair be parse_distance_length_pair with element as element
            Let start_position be length of decompressed minus pair.distance
            
            For i from 0 to pair.length minus 1:
                Let byte_to_copy be decompressed[start_position plus i]
                Add byte_to_copy to decompressed
        Otherwise:
            Add element to decompressed
        
        Set position to position plus 1
    
    Return decompressed

Process called "huffman_encode" that takes data as List[Integer] and compression_level as Integer returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Huffman coding for optimal bit-level compression
    Let frequency_table be calculate_frequency_table with data as data
    Let huffman_tree be build_huffman_tree with frequencies as frequency_table
    Let code_table be generate_huffman_codes with tree as huffman_tree
    
    Let encoded_bits be list containing
    For each byte in data:
        Let code be code_table[byte]
        Add code to encoded_bits
    
    Let packed_bytes be pack_bits_to_bytes with bits as encoded_bits
    Let header be create_huffman_header with code_table as code_table
    
    Return concatenate_byte_arrays with arrays as list containing header, packed_bytes

Process called "huffman_decode" that takes data as List[Integer] returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Huffman decoding to restore original data
    Let header_parse_result be parse_huffman_header with data as data
    If header_parse_result is None:
        Return None
    
    Let code_table be header_parse_result.code_table
    Let encoded_data be header_parse_result.encoded_data
    
    Let bit_stream be unpack_bytes_to_bits with bytes as encoded_data
    Let decoded_bytes be list containing
    Let current_code be ""
    
    For each bit in bit_stream:
        Set current_code to current_code plus bit
        If code_table contains current_code:
            Let decoded_byte be code_table[current_code]
            Add decoded_byte to decoded_bytes
            Set current_code to ""
    
    Return decoded_bytes
:End Note

Note: GZIP Header and Trailer Processing
Process called "create_gzip_header" that takes config as GZIPConfig and original_size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let header be list containing
    
    Add 31 to header  Note: Magic number byte 1 (0x1f)
    Add 139 to header  Note: Magic number byte 2 (0x8b)
    Add 8 to header   Note: Compression method (DEFLATE)
    
    Let flags be 0
    If config.preserve_filename and config.original_filename is not None:
        Set flags to flags plus 8  Note: FNAME flag
    If config.preserve_timestamp:
        Set flags to flags plus 4  Note: MTIME flag
    Add flags to header
    
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    If config.preserve_timestamp:
        Let timestamp_bytes be convert_integer_to_4_bytes with value as timestamp
        For each byte in timestamp_bytes:
            Add byte to header
    Otherwise:
        Add 0 to header  Note: MTIME byte 1
        Add 0 to header  Note: MTIME byte 2
        Add 0 to header  Note: MTIME byte 3
        Add 0 to header  Note: MTIME byte 4
    
    Let extra_flags be 0
    If config.compression_level is equal to 1:
        Set extra_flags to 4  Note: Fastest compression
    Otherwise if config.compression_level is equal to 9:
        Set extra_flags to 2  Note: Best compression
    Add extra_flags to header
    
    Add 255 to header  Note: Operating system (unknown)
    
    If config.preserve_filename and config.original_filename is not None:
        Let filename_bytes be convert_string_to_null_terminated_bytes with string as config.original_filename
        For each byte in filename_bytes:
            Add byte to header
    
    Return header

Process called "create_gzip_trailer" that takes crc32 as String and original_size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let trailer be list containing
    
    Let crc32_bytes be convert_crc32_to_bytes with crc32 as crc32
    For each byte in crc32_bytes:
        Add byte to trailer
    
    Let size_bytes be convert_integer_to_4_bytes with value as original_size
    For each byte in size_bytes:
        Add byte to trailer
    
    Return trailer

Process called "parse_gzip_data" that takes data as List[Integer] returns Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Try:
        If length of data is less than 18:  Note: Minimum GZIP file size
            Return None
        
        Let position be 0
        Let header_result be parse_gzip_header_at_position with data as data and position as position
        If header_result is None:
            Return None
        
        Set position to header_result.next_position
        Let compressed_data_end be length of data minus 8  Note: Trailer is 8 bytes
        Let compressed_data be slice_byte_array with:
            data as data
            start as position
            end as compressed_data_end
        
        Let trailer_start be compressed_data_end
        Let trailer be slice_byte_array with:
            data as data
            start as trailer_start
            end as length of data
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "header" as header_result.header
            "compressed_data" as compressed_data
            "trailer" as trailer
    
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "validate_gzip_data" that takes data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let errors be list containing
    
    If length of data is less than 18:
        Add "GZIP file too small (minimum 18 bytes)" to errors
    
    If length of data is greater than 1 and data[0] is not equal to 31:
        Add "Invalid magic number (first byte)" to errors
    
    If length of data is greater than 2 and data[1] is not equal to 139:
        Add "Invalid magic number (second byte)" to errors
    
    If length of data is greater than 3 and data[2] is not equal to 8:
        Add "Unsupported compression method (only DEFLATE supported)" to errors
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "is_valid" as length of errors is equal to 0
        "error_message" as join_list with list as errors and separator as "; "
        "suggestions" as list containing "Verify file is valid GZIP format", "Check for file corruption"
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "create_default_gzip_config" returns GZIPConfig:
    Return GZIPConfig with:
        compression_level as 6
        enable_crc_check as true
        enable_progress_tracking as false
        buffer_size as 65536
        enable_parallel_compression as false
        thread_count as 1
        preserve_filename as false
        preserve_timestamp as false
        original_filename as None
        compression_strategy as "default"
        window_bits as 15
        memory_level as 8
        enable_stream_mode as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_deflate_config_from_gzip_config" that takes config as GZIPConfig returns DeflateConfig:
    Return DeflateConfig with:
        compression_level as config.compression_level
        window_bits as config.window_bits
        memory_level as config.memory_level
        strategy as config.compression_strategy
        buffer_size as config.buffer_size divided by 2
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "validate_gzip_config" that takes config as GZIPConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let errors be list containing
    
    If config.compression_level is less than 1 or config.compression_level is greater than 9:
        Add "Compression level must be between 1 and 9" to errors
    
    If config.window_bits is less than 9 or config.window_bits is greater than 15:
        Add "Window bits must be between 9 and 15" to errors
    
    If config.memory_level is less than 1 or config.memory_level is greater than 9:
        Add "Memory level must be between 1 and 9" to errors
    
    If config.buffer_size is less than 1024:
        Add "Buffer size must be at least 1024 bytes" to errors
    
    If config.thread_count is less than 1:
        Add "Thread count must be at least 1" to errors
    
    Let valid_strategies be list containing "default", "filtered", "huffman_only", "rle", "fixed"
    If not valid_strategies contains config.compression_strategy:
        Add "Invalid compression strategy" to errors
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "is_valid" as length of errors is equal to 0
        "error_message" as join_list with list as errors and separator as "; "
        "suggestions" as list containing "Check GZIP configuration parameters", "Use create_default_gzip_config for valid defaults"

Process called "calculate_crc32" that takes data as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Calculate CRC32 checksum using IEEE 802.3 polynomial
    Let crc be 4294967295  Note: 0xFFFFFFFF
    Let crc_table be get_crc32_table
    
    For each byte in data:
        Let table_index be (crc xor byte) and 255
        Set crc to (crc shifted right by 8) xor crc_table[table_index]
    
    Set crc to crc xor 4294967295  Note: 0xFFFFFFFF
    Return convert_integer_to_hex_string with value as crc

Process called "calculate_crc32_incremental" that takes previous_crc32 as String and data as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Calculate incremental CRC32 for streaming operations
    Let crc be convert_hex_string_to_integer with hex as previous_crc32
    Let crc_table be get_crc32_table
    
    For each byte in data:
        Let table_index be (crc xor byte) and 255
        Set crc to (crc shifted right by 8) xor crc_table[table_index]
    
    Return convert_integer_to_hex_string with value as crc

Process called "convert_string_to_bytes" that takes data as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert string to byte array using UTF-8 encoding
    Let bytes be list containing
    For each character in data:
        Let char_code be get_character_code with character as character
        Add char_code to bytes
    Return bytes

Process called "convert_bytes_to_string" that takes bytes as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Convert byte array to string using UTF-8 encoding
    Let result be ""
    For each byte_value in bytes:
        Let character be get_character_from_code with code as byte_value
        Set result to result plus character
    Return result

Process called "calculate_compression_ratio" that takes original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer returns Float:
    If original_size is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    Return compressed_size divided by original_size

Process called "concatenate_byte_arrays" that takes arrays as List[List[Integer]] returns List[Integer]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each array in arrays:
        For each byte in array:
            Add byte to result
    Return result

Process called "generate_gzip_stream_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_time
    Let random_suffix be generate_random_string with length as 8
    Return "gzip_stream_" plus timestamp plus "_" plus random_suffix

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current UNIX timestamp as integer seconds since epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds as Integer

Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure random string using system random
    Return system_call_generate_random_string with length as length

Process called "check_file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists using system file operations
    Return system_call_file_exists with path as path

Process called "get_file_size" that takes path as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get file size in bytes using system file operations
    Return system_call_get_file_size with path as path

Process called "get_directory_from_path" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Extract directory path from full file path using system path operations
    Return system_call_get_directory_path with path as path

Process called "ensure_directory_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Create directory and parent directories if needed using system operations
    Return system_call_create_directory_recursive with path as path

Process called "get_filename_from_path" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Extract filename from full file path using system path operations
    Return system_call_get_filename_from_path with path as path

Process called "get_character_code" that takes character as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get UTF-8 code point from character using system encoding functions
    Return system_call_character_to_utf8_code with character as character

Process called "get_character_from_code" that takes code as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert UTF-8 code point to character using system encoding functions
    Return system_call_utf8_code_to_character with code as code

Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Join list of strings with separator
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result

